 <sect1 xml:id="sec.deployment.docupdates.sle12_sp1_maint1">
  <title>March 2016 (Maintenance Release of &productname; 12 SP1)</title>
  <para/>
  <variablelist>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
    <term><xref linkend="cha.zseries"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>Mentioned requirement for a local X server and instructions for
        Microsoft Windows (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=956059"/>).</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>Renamed <command>zpxe.exec</command> to <command>zpxe.rexx</command>
       and rephrased sentence regarding correct place (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=867809"/>).</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>Added note about z/VM 6.3 regarding installation of APAR VM65419
        (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=958054"/>).</para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.advdisk"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>Distinguish between remote and local repository more clearly
     (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=956058"/>).</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>Added note about reformatting partitions with
      <command>mkswap</command>, because initrd image cannot boot up when
      swap partition has changed (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=955822"/>).</para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </sect1>

 <sect1 xml:id="sec.deployment.docupdates.sle12_sp1">
  <title>December 2015 (Initial Release of &productname; 12 SP1)</title>
   <!--list of general issues that apply to all books-->
  <xi:include href="common_docupdates_sp1_i.xml"/>
  <variablelist>
   <!-- 2. Installation on AMD64 and Intel 64 -->
   <varlistentry os="sles">
    <term><xref linkend="cha.x86" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed pointers to the <guimenu>Failsafe</guimenu> boot option, which
        has been removed (Fate #317016).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <!-- 4 Installation on IBM System z -->
   <varlistentry os="sles">
    <term><xref linkend="cha.zseries" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added installation instruction for KVM guests (FATE 319264).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.prep.boot_procedure"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- 6. Installation with YaST -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.inst" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.start.parameters.proxy"/>
        (Fate #318488).</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added a warning on using unsigned drivers in secure boot mode to <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.bootscreen_uefi"/> (Fate #317593).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- 8 Installing or Removing Software -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.y2.sw" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added <xref linkend="sec.y2.sw.deps.recommends"/> (Fate #318099).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- 10. Installing Add-On Products  -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.add-ons" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated chapter to reflect the software changes to the former &yast;
         <guimenu>&scc; Configuration</guimenu> dialog (now called
         <guimenu>Product Registration</guimenu>) and the &yast;
         <guimenu>Add-On Products</guimenu> module (Fate #318800).</para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- 14. Advanced Disk Setup -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.advdisk" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
    <itemizedlist>
     <listitem>
       <para>
        Mentioned that subvolumes for
         <filename>/var/lib/mariadb</filename>,
         <filename>/var/lib/pgsql</filename>, and
         <filename>/var/lib/libvirt/images</filename> are created with the
        option <literal>no copy on write</literal> by default to avoid extensive
        fragmenting with Btrfs.
       </para>
     </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Subscription Management</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        The chapter about registering clients at a &smtool; server has been
        replaced by <xref linkend="smt.client" xrefstyle="select:title"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <!-- III Updating and Upgrading SUSE Linux Enterprise -->
   <varlistentry>
       <term><xref linkend="part.update" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/></term>
       <listitem>
         <itemizedlist>
           <listitem>
             <para>Split former update chapter into several independent
               chapters and combined them under this new part.</para>
           </listitem>
           <listitem>
            <para>Removed &yast; Wagon chapter, as  &yast; Wagon is unsupported for
               &productname; &productnumber;.</para>
           </listitem>
           <listitem>
             <para>Added new chapter: <xref linkend="cha.update.spmigration"/>.</para>
           </listitem>
           <listitem>
             <para>Added
               <xref linkend="sec.update.prep.mariadb"/> and
               <xref linkend="sec.update.prep.postgresql"/>.</para>
           </listitem>
           <listitem>
             <para>Integrated various new features: Fate #315161,
               Fate #318636,
               Fate #319128,
               Fate #319129,
               Fate #319138,
               Fate #319140.
             </para>
           </listitem>
         </itemizedlist>
       </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Bugfixes</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem os="sles">
       <para>
        Fixed path to <filename>zpxe.exec</filename>  (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=937511"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem os="sles">
       <para>
        Added the <literal>https</literal> protocol to <xref
        linkend="sec.appdendix.parm.yast2"/> (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=951421"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Consistent use of <command>yast</command>,
        <command>yast2.ssh</command>, <command>yast.ssh</command> for SSH
        based installation (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=956060"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Consistent spelling of boot parameters (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=956054"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        PowerKVM: virt-install does not know about SLES12 (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=880918"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        IBM &ppc;: Starting an Xserver after an Upgrade
        (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=948980"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added documentation on the boot process for IBM &zseries; (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=942772"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Description of encrypted <filename>/</filename> and
        <filename>/boot</filename> on Btrfs was missing. Added an important
        note in <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.inst_mode.partitioning"/> and <xref
        linkend="yast2.btrfs"/> (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=926951"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Zypper multiversion kernels should be mentioned for SP2 Update (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=753809"></link>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        SLES 12 Deployment Guide errors for zPXE installations (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=944384"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        AutoYaST hangs at "Configuring Bootloader ... 50%" with 512RAM (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=927237"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Netsetup Parameters Wrong (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=928792"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Documentation on not creating /usr as separate partition is missing
        (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=930267"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Document how to enable SELinux during install (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=928158"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        YaST boot loader: supported scenarios needs updating clarification
        (<link
        xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=939197"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  </sect1>

 <sect1 xml:id="sec.deployment.docupdates.sle12_ga_maint1">
  <title>February 2015 (Documentation Maintenance Update)</title>

  <variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.timezone" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      With NTP disabled it is recommended to avoid writing system time to
      the hardware clock. Thus set <literal>SYSTOHC=no</literal>.
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Bugfixes</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Adjustments for SMT because of the switch from &ncc; to &scc; (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=857639"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        <xref linkend="sec.y2.userman.adv.passw"/>: Password Settings,
        Expiration Date is expiring user accounts in YAST Users module
        (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=743874"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Various bugfixes for <xref linkend="cha.update.sle"/>:
       </para>
       <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          The named upgrade path does not work there is no working upgrade
          path from SLES 11 SP3 to SLES 12 on Linux for System z
          (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=907648"/>).
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          [doc] 7.5 The Atomic Update
          (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=905330"/>).
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          [doc] 7.5 Upgrading to SLE 12
          (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=904188"/>).
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          [doc] 7.4 Intermediate step: Updating SLE 11 SP2 to SLE 11 SP3
          (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=904186"/>).
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          [doc] 7.2 Supported Upgrade Paths to SLE
          (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=904182"/>).
         </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
         <para>
          [doc] Potentially misleading info around the 6-months overlap in
          support
          (<link xlink:href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=902463"/>).
         </para>
        </listitem>
       </itemizedlist>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </sect1>
 <sect1 xml:id="sec.deployment.docupdates.sle12_ga">
  <title>October 2014 (Initial Release of &productname; 12)</title>
  <!--list of general issues that apply to all books-->
   <xi:include href="common_docupdates_ga_i.xml"/>
  <variablelist>
<!-- 2. Installation on AMD64 and Intel 64 -->
   <varlistentry os="sles">
    <term><xref linkend="cha.x86"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist mark="bullet" spacing="normal">
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated system requirements.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
<!-- 3. Installation on IBM POWER  -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.power"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added POWER8 to the list of supported hardware (Fate #315272).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        &sls; 12 for POWER has moved to Little Endian. Updated affected
        parts of the documentation.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
<!-- 4. Installation on IBM System z -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.zseries"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated the list of supported platforms: Removed IBM Series z9 and
        z10 machines and added IBM zEnterprise BC12.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated the memory and disk space requirements.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed instructions on how to IPL from tape&mdash;this is no
        longer supported.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Rewrote large parts of <xref linkend="sec.prep.netcfg"/> to remove
        redundant information and make it more concise.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed references to Token Ring, which is no longer supported
        (Fate #313154).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 6. Installation with YaST -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.inst"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Completely rewrote the chapter because of the new installation
        workflow.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        The installation routine now supports setting up multiple network
        devices during the installation (Fate #315680):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.network"/>
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        The installation proposal contains a separate
        <filename>/home</filename> partition formatted with XFS (Fate #316637
        and Fate #316624):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.inst_mode.partitioning"/>
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed occurrences of the &yast; Repair module which has been
        dropped (Fate #308670).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Update repositories are added after having registered with &scc;
        and can be used during installation (Fate #312012):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.inst_mode.addon"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Extensions and modules can be added to the system during the
        installation (Fate #316548):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.conf.manual.cc"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        &sled; can be installed as an add-on on top of &sls;
        (Fate #316436): <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.inst_mode.addon"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem os="sles">
       <para>
        The HW crypto stack for IBM &zseries; can be selected for
        installation via a pattern (Fate #316143):
        <xref linkend="sec.i.yast2.proposal.sofware"/>
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Automatically importing SSH keys from a previous installation can be
        disabled (Fate #314982).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 7. Updating SUSE Linux Enterprise -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.update.sle"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added new section: <xref linkend="sec.update.sle12"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 8. Setting Up Hardware Components with YaST -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.y2.hw"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed the following sections as the respective &yast; modules
        are no longer included: <citetitle>Hardware Information</citetitle>,
        <citetitle>Setting Up Graphics Card and Monitor</citetitle>,
        <citetitle>Mouse Model</citetitle>, and <citetitle>Setting Up a
        Scanner</citetitle>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed content about mouse setup and adjusted
        <xref linkend="cha.y2.hw.keym"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 9. Installing or Removing Software -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.y2.sw"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Completely rewrote <xref linkend="sec.updater"/> because of changes
        in the &gnome; software updater.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 10. Installing Add-On Products  -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.add-ons"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Installing add-on products or software extensions is now also
        possible without access to physical media. Added the following new
        sections: <xref linkend="sec.update.registersystem"/> and
        <xref linkend="sec.add-ons.extensions"/>. Modified
        <xref linkend="sec.add-ons.install"/> accordingly.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- 16. Subscription Management -->
    <term>Subscription Management</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        For registering clients against an &smt; server,
        <command>suse_register</command> has been replaced with
        <command>SUSEConnect</command> (Fate #316585).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Bugfixes</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated section <xref linkend="sec.updater"/> according to
        <link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=839692"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed section <citetitle>Using Fingerprint
        Authentication</citetitle>. Further minor corrections and additions
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=857680"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed obsolete parameter <literal>OsaMedium</literal> from
        parmfile and Cobbler examples
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=860404"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added instructions on how to add secondary languages during
        installation
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=870482"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Multiversion feature (more than one kernel installed) is enabled by
        default
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=891805"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Warn about incompatible Kernel Module Packages (KPMs)
        (<link xlink:href="http://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=891805"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </sect1>
